key_points: Gabby Petito's cause of death was determined to be strangulation by Teton County Coroner Dr. Brent Blue.
Petito's remains were found at a campground in the Bridger-Teton National Forest, likely outside for 3 to 4 weeks before discovery.
The exact time of Gabby Petito's death will not be determined, only the cause and manner of death were identified.
Brian Laundrie, Gabby Petito's fiancé, is considered a person of interest in her case and remains missing.
Dr. Brent Blue mentioned tests including a whole-body CAT scan and toxicology reports were conducted before concluding the autopsy.
Gabby Petito was not pregnant at the time of her death.
Gabby's parents believe Brian Laundrie is alive and in hiding, calling him a 'coward'.
North Port plans a permanent memorial for Gabby Petito, replacing a makeshift memorial with a steel bench.
Laundrie's attorney stated Gabby Petito's death is a tragedy and emphasized Laundrie is only a person of interest regarding her demise.
Authorities are still searching for Brian Laundrie, receiving assistance from his father, and urges public to provide any information.
spokespersons: Steven Bertolino (Attorney for the Laundrie family)
